{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Workflow\/documentation\/Workflow\/RenderContext","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RenderContext","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RenderContext","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"RenderContext","modules":[{"name":"Workflow"}],"symbolKind":"class","externalID":"s:8Workflow13RenderContextC","roleHeading":"Class"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"RenderContext"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"WorkflowType"},{"kind":"text","text":"> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"WorkflowType"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Workflow\/documentation\/Workflow\/Workflow","preciseIdentifier":"s:8WorkflowAAP","text":"Workflow"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"During a render pass, a workflow may want to defer to a child"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"workflow to render some portion of its content. For example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a workflow that renders to a split-screen view model might"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to child A for the left side, and child B for the right"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"side view models. Nesting allows for a fractal tree that is constructed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"out of many small parts."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a parent wants to delegate to a child workflow, it must first","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"create an instance of that workflow. This can be thought of as the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"model of the child workflow. It does not contain any active state,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it simply contains the data necessary to create or update a workflow","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"node.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The parent then calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"render(workflow:outputMap:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with two values:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The child workflow."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A closure that transforms the child’s output events into the parent’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Event"},{"type":"text","text":" type so that the parent can respond to events generated by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the child."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the parent had previously rendered a child of the same type, the existing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"child workflow node is updated.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the parent had not rendered a child of the same type in the previous"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"render pass, a new child workflow node is generated."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The infrastructure then performs a render pass on the child to obtain its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"Rendering","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value, which is then returned to the caller."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Workflow\/documentation\/Workflow\/RenderContext\/make